Description: Heavily corroded copper alloy rectangular plate, slightly convex, possibly from an armour, with a longitudinal double mid-ridge on top, made of two angle plates welded side to side. Five small round fxing holes were perforated falong the edge of both shortest sides, .
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.74, p.184, pl.26)
Condition: poor, incomplete (three corners and part of one side broken and missing)
